Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced) into half moons. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{10%g} (stalks and all). Roll the @Tuscan pork sausage{250%g} meat into three meatballs per person.

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add in the meatballs. Fry, turning occasionally until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove to a #plate{} and set aside - keep the pan!

Put a large saucepan on medium heat with a splash of @oil{splash}. Add the onion and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and the @fennel seeds{1/2%tbsp} and cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} to the pan, refill the tin(s) a quarter with water, give it a good swirl around to get all the tomato out and add this to the pan, along with a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @black pepper{pinch} and a sprinkle of @?sugar{(some)}. Gently return the meatballs to the pan and simmer over medium-low heat until the sauce is thick and tomatoey, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @linguine{200%g} to the boiling pan of water and cook for ~{6%minutes} or until 'al dente', then drain in a #colander{}.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through, but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

Serve the meatballs and the rich tomato sauce piled on top of the linguine. Add a sprinkling of parsley and grate over the @parmesan cheese{20%g}. Tuck in!